---
// src/pages/livros/catholicism.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { getEstimatedReadingTimeLabel } from '../../lib/reading-time';

const bookMeta = {
    layoutTitle: 'Catholicism - Recomendação de Livro',
    headingTitle: 'Catholicism',
    subtitle: 'A Journey to the Heart of the Faith (Second Edition)',
    description: 'Resenha do livro Catholicism, de Bishop Robert Barron, com visão geral da obra, principais temas e recomendações de leitura.',
    readingSource: `
Catholicism. A Journey to the Heart of the Faith.
Sobre o Livro. Novidades na Segunda Edição.
O Que Estão Dizendo. Índice.
Sobre o Autor.
`,
};

const bookReadTime = getEstimatedReadingTimeLabel(bookMeta.readingSource);
---

<Layout title={bookMeta.layoutTitle} description={bookMeta.description}>
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Book Header -->
        <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="inline-block mb-6">
                <h2 class="text-sm font-bold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider">Recomendação de Livro</h2>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Book Details Section -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
            <!-- Book Cover & Info -->
            <div class="md:col-span-1">
                <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg overflow-hidden border border-gray-800 sticky top-8">
                    <img 
                        src="https://bookstore.wordonfire.org/cdn/shop/files/2508_Catholicism_2nd-Edition_A__SQUARE-1000x1000_MT-2.jpg?v=1758313508&width=500"
                        alt="Catholicism: A Journey to the Heart of the Faith"
                        class="w-full aspect-[3/4] object-cover"
                    />
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <div class="mb-6">
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">Autor</p>
                            <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Bishop Robert Barron</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mb-6">
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">Formato</p>
                            <p class="text-white">Capa Dura / Audiobook</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mb-6">
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">Preço</p>
                            <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-400">$23.96</p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 line-through">$29.95</p>
                            <p class="text-xs text-green-400 font-semibold mt-2">20% OFF</p>
                        </div>
                        <a 
                            href="https://bookstore.wordonfire.org/products/catholicism"
                            target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener noreferrer"
                            class="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition block text-center"
                        >
                            Comprar no Word on Fire
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Book Content -->
            <div class="md:col-span-2">
                <div class="mb-8">
                    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-4">
                        {bookMeta.headingTitle}
                    </h1>
                    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-300 font-serif italic mb-6">
                        {bookMeta.subtitle}
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">{bookReadTime}</p>
                    <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-6 py-4 bg-gray-900 rounded-r-lg">
                        <p class="text-gray-200 text-lg italic">
                            "What I propose to do in this book is to take you on a guided exploration of the Catholic world... conducting you ever deeper into the mystery of the Incarnation."
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-3">— Bishop Barron, from the introduction</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- About the Book -->
                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-4">Sobre o Livro</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        <p>
                            O que é o Catolicismo? Uma tradição viva de dois mil anos? Uma cosmovisão? Um modo de vida? Um relacionamento? Um mistério? Em <strong>Catholicism</strong>, o Bispo Robert Barron examina todas essas questões e mais, buscando capturar o corpo, coração e mente da fé católica.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Partindo da fundação essencial da Encarnação, vida e ensinamentos de Jesus Cristo, o Bispo Barron percorre os elementos definidores do Catolicismo — desde sacramento, adoração e oração, até Maria, os Apóstolos e santos, graça, salvação, céu e inferno — usando sua compreensão distinta e dinâmica de arte, literatura, arquitetura, histórias pessoais, Escritura, teologia, filosofia e história para apresentar a Igreja ao mundo.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Emparelhado com sua série de documentários do mesmo título, <strong>Catholicism</strong> é uma jornada íntima capturando "a coisa católica" em toda sua profundidade e beleza. Eclético, único e inspirador, o Bispo Barron traz a fé à vida para uma nova geração em um estilo que é fiel às verdades atemporais enquanto simultaneamente fala na linguagem da vida contemporânea.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- New in Second Edition -->
                <section class="bg-blue-900 border border-blue-800 p-6 rounded-lg mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-4">✦ Novidades na Segunda Edição</h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-200">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Um prefácio novo do Bispo Barron</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Imagens em cores cheias de arte sagrada e catedrais deslumbrantes</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Uma bibliografia abrangente</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Notas expandidas do Bispo Barron</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Um índice de Escritura</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-blue-400 mr-3 mt-1">•</span>
                            <span>Um índice de assunto revisado</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <!-- What People Say -->
                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-6">O Que Estão Dizendo</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-6 py-4">
                            <p class="text-gray-300 italic mb-3">
                                "Clarity, intelligence, passion, and elegance—these are the marks of a writer in top form, and Bishop Barron brings all these gifts to bear in this extraordinary reflection on the Catholic faith. If you read one book this year on what Catholics believe and why, this is the book to read—and to share with others."
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 font-semibold">— Archbishop Charles J. Chaput, OFM Cap.</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Archbishop Emeritus of Philadelphia</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-6 py-4">
                            <p class="text-gray-300 italic mb-3">
                                "Bishop Robert Barron's great gift is to wed intellectual depth with clarity and vividness of expression. His Catholicism is a superb exploration of the Catholic vision that seamlessly unites theological reflection and masterpieces of architecture and art."
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 font-semibold">— Robert P. Imbelli</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Associate Professor Emeritus of Theology, Boston College</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-6 py-4">
                            <p class="text-gray-300 italic mb-3">
                                "Catholicism is one of the most significant efforts ever to advance what Pope John Paul II called 'the New Evangelization.'"
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 font-semibold">— George Weigel</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Author of Witness to Hope and The End and the Beginning</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Table of Contents -->
        <section class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-6">Índice</h2>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-3">Introdução</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">→</span>
                                <span>Prefácio para a Segunda Edição</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">→</span>
                                <span>Introdução: A Coisa Católica</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Capítulos</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">1.</span>
                                <span>Amazed and Afraid: The Revelation of God Become Man</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">2.</span>
                                <span>Happy Are We: The Teachings of Jesus</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">3.</span>
                                <span>That Than Which Nothing Greater Can Be Thought: The Ineffable Mystery of God</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">4.</span>
                                <span>Our Tainted Nature's Solitary Boast: Mary, the Mother of God</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">5.</span>
                                <span>The Indispensable Men: Peter, Paul, and the Missionary Adventure</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">6.</span>
                                <span>A Body Both Suffering and Glorious: The Mystical Union of Christ and the Church</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">7.</span>
                                <span>Word Made Flesh, True Bread of Heaven: The Mystery of the Church's Sacrament and Worship</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">8.</span>
                                <span>A Vast Company of Witnesses: The Communion of Saints</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">9.</span>
                                <span>The Fire of His Love: Prayer and the Life of the Spirit</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">10.</span>
                                <span>World Without End: The Last Things</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">•</span>
                                <span>Coda: It's All About God</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h3 class="text-blue-400 font-semibold mb-3 mt-6">Outros</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 text-sm">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">•</span>
                                <span>Notas</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">•</span>
                                <span>Bibliografia</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">•</span>
                                <span>Índice de Escritura</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-blue-400 mr-2">•</span>
                                <span>Índice de Assuntos</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- About the Author -->
        <section class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-8 mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-4">Sobre o Autor</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                <strong class="text-white">Bishop Robert Barron</strong> é o fundador da Word on Fire Catholic Ministries e apresentador de CATHOLICISM, uma série de documentários inovadora e premiada sobre a fé católica. Em 21 de julho de 2015, o Papa Francisco anunciou sua nomeação como Bispo Auxiliar na Arquidiocese de Los Angeles, e em 2 de junho de 2022, nomeou o Bispo Barron o nono bispo da Diocese de Winona-Rochester (Minnesota). Ordenado em 1986 na Arquidiocese de Chicago, o Bispo Barron recebeu um mestrado em filosofia da Universidade Católica da América em 1982 e um doutorado em teologia sagrada do Institut Catholique de Paris em 1992.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900 to-blue-800 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-white mb-4">Pronto para começar?</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-200 mb-6 text-lg">
                Explore a profundidade e beleza da fé católica com esta obra transformadora.
            </p>
            <a 
                href="https://bookstore.wordonfire.org/products/catholicism"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-block bg-white text-blue-900 px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-bold hover:bg-gray-100 transition"
            >
                Comprar Agora no Word on Fire →
            </a>
            <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm mt-4">
                💚 Frete grátis para os EUA | Formato: Hardcover ou Audiobook
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</Layout>
